review_blob: Swetet carmelized nose, looks dark tan to brown and hazy, sweet on palate, not overly so like the DF head 120 minute, 100 IBUs pleasant rantehr than distracting, nice amount of sugar/malts cover/balance the hops, sweet and dry asrtingent finish, SOLID beer

The ultimate in craft beer.  Beer geeks rejoice, a blend of 5 different oak aged beers layer intense and subtle flavors together of malted cramel sweet fruit mild chocolate covered with burbon barrel aging, and just the right amount.
Sweet pine aroma, cloudy light brown with solid head.  Sweet and balanced IPA, surprisingly good out of a can.  Off dry finish
Solid amber ale.  Poured medium brown with a thin head and nice hop aroma.  Mildly sweet and well balanced biterness make this beer a great session beer
Piney aroma clouded light brown color super smooth medium weight creamy body
Sweet hoppy malty red ale. Pours with redish pink head.  Full round and sweet this beer is a touchdown.

brillant malted coffee aroma, pours jet black with nie head.  Tastes of soured coffee on the front which is actually quite nice then finishes with complex roasted malt flavors, definately DO NOT drink it cold, a huge an impressive beer
clear yellow, standard mega beer from/for one country almost notihing flavor wise to talk about, just "a" beer, unimpressive in every way
Sweet hoppy aroma Pale golden blonde color, strong citrus flavors on front nice sweetness in the middle and a solid hop finish
beer_name: Stone 20th Anniversary Encore Series: 08.08.08 Vertical Epic Ale

review_blob: Thin pink head, sparkling, cherry bomb nose.  Sweet and crisp, nice tart acidity balances this beer out from just beer fruity.  Solid Belgian yeasty finish.
Litle to no aroma, super smooth session beer.  Nice and round sweetness, no noticeable hops
Bottle, dark brown black pour into belgian tulip glass.  Nice toffee flavor mixed with hints of rum-like fruit, layered with flavor.  This beer is not too heavy and opened up nicely.
Draft beer. Full colored translucent yellow with a nice yet quickly fading head.  Simple in style lightly hopped Pils.  A good drinker

BLUEBERRY!  It wants to be a lambic, actually suprisingly good beer fruit beer considering its an AB InBev product.  Pours  purple blue, and is sparkling.  Super Sweet. If you want a fruity ice cold blueberry beer, this is it.
Thin nutty aroma, the hazelnut is more in the finish and not in the mid palate.  Super smooth brown ale, very light body.
Wow what a bad beer, this one hit the drain.  Was a sample from a beer rep at a beer tasting.  He was pretty embarrassed at how bad this beer tastes.

Tulip glass on tap at Ground Control in Goodyear AZ.  Nice 2-3 finger head.  Cloudly yellow hue. Solid yeasty belgian aroma.  Tastes super smooth slight-medium sweetness with a nice like clove spice kick.

Sweet yeasty aroma.  Poured with a nice thick creamy head.  heavy amber color.  Creamy on the palate with a long smooth cleam finish.  Nice malted flavor.  A very good balance between the malt and the hops.  Super drinkablility
beer_name: Bear Republic Hop Rod Rye Ale

review_blob: Hoppy floral nose with some pine.  Medium to dark amber, pours with thin to no head.  Tastes on seet pine with a medium sweet somewhat spicey malted finish.  Clean buttery finish
Not a bad thing to say about this barely wine.  Its super smooth medium bodied and very very good to drink.  Full of malted sweetness coated with oaky vanilla in a very long finish
beer_name: AleSmith Old Numbskull - Bourbon Barrel Aged

review_blob: Way over the top.  I drink alot of IPAs and this was too much.  The hops were almost sour they were so bitter.  Full bodied and defiantly a heavy beer, the 90 minute hits the mark for DFs best
The first of 3F beers I had and it was a good warm up, one fo the best Irish ales Ive had citrus aroma full bodied for an ale an a nice clean finish
A decent anniversary beer not quite as over the top great as the others.  Still quite good medium abmer, the jasmine wasnt to overbearing.
beer_name: Three Floyds Fantabulous Resplendence (XI Anniversary Ale)

review_blob: Super nose of pine chased by sweet citrus.  Hazy amber. Definate malted nut taste nut covered up by the hops.  This is such a good IPA
Just a graet all around pale ale.  Medium hoppy nose, nice sweet floral notes. Some really good carmel notes on the finished layered with mild bitterness.

The aroma was great.  It poured inky black with a tiny cream head.  Definately charred oak on the front of the palate, vanilla in the middle palate and smoke all the way through.  For a bourbon aged stout at 150 days I would ahve expected the flavors to have mellowed a bit more than they did.  It wasindeed a strong full flavored beer with very sharp flavors.  Drink this one around 50 degrees.
